description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Information Officer (Reporting &amp; Standards)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At BCU Health Board we believe that data helps save lives and improves outcomes for patients. Working with doctors and nurses to understand what matters for their patients the Information Department has developed analytics that help our clinicians make better decisions and improve their services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic professional to undertake the role of Information Officer within our Reporting &amp; Standards Team. If data is to be trusted for decision making it needs to be of a high quality, with users educated to collect robust, accurate data in real time. The successful candidate will be required to work independently and as part of the Reporting &amp; Standards Team; prioritising their own workload to ensure effectiveness and efficiency in delivering objectives whilst working with minimum supervision. They should possess good organisation and communication skills and be able to work under pressure and to deadlines. They should also be familiar with Microsoft applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is keen to learn, numerate and curious with great attention to detail and the ability to absorb lots of new information. We offer a full induction and training package, flexible working hours and good future career opportunities. We are proud of our fantastic team ethic, which sees us all pulling together to make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think this is the opportunity you are looking for to progress your career and want to hear more about joining our friendly and welcoming team then please contact the following for more information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sharon.Cartwright@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bethan.E.Jones2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that due to COVID-19 and Welsh Government’s guidance on social distancing your interview will almost certainly be carried out via Microsoft Teams or Skype. If this is the case, you will be notified in advance so that if you do not have the app you can download it to your phone or computer/laptop. The download is free of charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Sharon Cartwright Job title Specialist Information Analyst&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address sharon.cartwright@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bethan Ellis Jones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bethan.E.Jones2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
